},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=OgimALORcqxZygRAkGbe4w\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=135.96869\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"/url?q=https://seattlesounddental.com/\u0026opi=79508299\u0026sa=U\u0026ved=0ahUKEwixlIq0yr-UAxW3K0QIHeCsD6sQqRkIICgT\u0026usg=AOvVaw1XbKuFS6hX3-DEdXErF3Ut","source":"seattlesounddental.com"},"owner":{"id":"111703910555880372048","name":"Seattle Sound Dental - Downtown (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111703910555880372048"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Central Business District","street":"509 Olive Wy #1024","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98101","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"crowd","name":"Crowd","options":[{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Kafiya Arte","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQJcM7mlj6fzpq0_AsBFQc6kVkJKCsR8UVirxLG46t6gELCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Two of my siblings and two of my close friends receive their dental care through Dr. Tanner. They rave about him all the time, so I knew that when I finally worked up the courage to see the dentist, I was going to see him. I’ve had a long time fear of dental procedures, and genuinely thought my loved ones were exaggerating over how much they loved Dr. Tanner. But I was completely wrong! Dr. Tanner is hands down the best dentist I could have ever imagined, let alone have the privilege to have experienced. He was thorough, educational, and efficient. He took the time to assess all of my dental needs in one visit, never rushed, and answered each and every one of my questions to completion. Somehow my follow-up treatment visit was even better! The procedure was painless, and he once again provided excellent education regarding what to expect during the healing process. I recovered well and am now able to enjoy food again. It was genuinely an incredible experience and I will be back regularly!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"D W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLcAkgQWU6RAAY7f1eOKFzWwYGH-AxV9V0yv5lVGghCNFAlbw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently moved to Seattle and I was looking for a dentist that was in my plan and I do read ratings/reviews . so I went to Seattle sound downtown Seattle and I love it!!!!!\nSome of the reviews stated that the office staff was not polite. I think they’re amazing. They were nice I’m very helpful with explaining their process and everything Then I met the doctor and he is awesome personality. Nice demeanor just very caring he listens you know and he explained the process and what would need to be done for a crown and everything.\n\nI even told my son that this dentist is great so he’s gonna look him up too👍🏼😉","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelcie Pittaluga","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4X2_5vhcnnU-bZa6WMWvGnhrLB76nyKrDlOLQ01ZI3JUBe1Asmg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As someone with debilitating dental anxiety, I can't say enough good things about this practice and every single member of their team! I've received phenomenal care from Dr. Tanner, Jesse, and Crystal after delaying regular visits due to a cross-country move and fears surrounding finding a team patient enough to deal with my extreme anxiety, and they've quickly converted me into a patient for life. Crystal in particular deserves a special shoutout - she is an absolute angel and could not be more patient or thoughtful, doing everything possible to put me at ease. I'm incredibly grateful to have found this practice, and can't recommend them highly enough!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matthew Armani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJt6-M_01s9ljT6CK0FeJHsG8Nscmgqy7_W-6Ta6oZzU0t7EA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went in extremely anxious due to past negative dental experiences, but the care I received completely changed that. I felt nothing but compassion and zero judgment, despite being very insecure about my teeth. A tooth that had caused me daily pain for years was saved with a root canal and crown instead of being pulled, and the result looks completely natural. I’m finally pain-free, confident enough to smile again, and no longer dread the dentist. I’m incredibly grateful to the staff and Dr. Nick Tanner for their exceptional care and highly recommend them. Special shoutout to Crystal as well.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ciji Munday","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDkyQHDUHSguGkrZ4Y2yoMjWuRbHkf5q2dK7dtNBoLhPNiw6w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Tanner and his staff are the best! They make you feel comfortable as soon as you arrive, and are really friendly and organized. Dr. Tanner listens well and is really good at explaining options, and the work he's doing which I really appreciate.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"LightInTheDark","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKI9o8jakU4qX_06H_vxzZN52dDFExzk5-iLg7JkhvHegbUnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Horrible experience! The secretary is rude and intimidating! I went there only because I was seeing another doctor in that same building. The doctor himself is nice! However, the whole experience with this office is not worth the money and the nightmare afterwards. You pay for everything they tell you to pay for before you leave their office just to learn years later...that apparently you somehow owe them something... but it's too late because they already sued you and now the initial insignificant amount that you didn't know you owe them has quadrupled because they sued you (legal fees for court hearing you didn't know you had, no opportunity to defend yourself in anyway) and you receive a letter with court decision to put lien on your already very small paycheck. Just be aware of them practicing dishonestly, and be aware that even after you paid for everything that they told you to pay for there will be more that they will want you to  pay. Just be aware of the possibility of this scenario. There are better dental offices out there thank God!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Courtney Bay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEMevc5mN8D3CkIhgT6bLmys6JWZYUNN7HKKrh8-k17Z5icxY9ew=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"EDIT IN RESPONSE TO THEIR REPLY:\nIt wont let me reply to their comment but choosing to literally GASLIGHT ME and my experience by claiming I have the wrong office is insane and another reason to not support this business. Instead of taking accountability, they choose to gaslight.\n\nI never said you sent me to collections - I said the first time you made me aware of late payment was a threat to go into collections if i dont pay. My apt was in March and this didnt get resolved until August.\n\nDO NOT BOOK HERE - if they make a mistake or treat you poorly they will then choose to gaslight and deny your entire experience instead of take constructive criticism to just do better. Disgusting behavior.\n\n--------\nORIGINAL REVIEW:\nDid not have a good experience here. The dental cleaning I got took a super long time and I wasn't being rinsed/suction at all until a whole half of my mouth was polished. I was pooling in my own saliva the entire time. It was just uncomfortable and felt unprofessional.\n\nInsurance was difficult to figure out - I provided the correct information and months after my cleaning kept receiving bills for being uninsured and notices that if I didnt pay I would go into collections. The conversations I had on the phone trying to figure this out I feel were a bit rude and I felt like I was being scammed for money. My insurance carrier had told me they never received anything from the dentist all those months and I had to get my employer/company broker involved to get to a resolution.\n\nI was also recommended to get 8 fillings - this didnt feel right especially since at that point my insurance issues were unresolved and they had advised to just do the fillings and handle insurance later. And there was just no way 8 was needed when I had no issues at previous dentist. I did not move forward and got a second opinion at another dentist in the area and they told me at best I needed 2 and they werent that urgent. The new dentist told me they had absolutely no idea where anyone could have gotten 8 even if they were being nitpicky.\n\nThe doctor himself was extremely kind - so I did appreciate that. But with the reco for unneeded fillings and just overall experience with the cleaning and office staff dealing with  insurance - I would not recommend going Here","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Larry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLnDrYFnW9doCk9CAG9Q8vTyD8WPE55772Nu62hRq8gU6I51A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I had a mixed experience here. The staff were unclear about the actual costs, and I left unsure what I might be billed later. A friend who recommended this office ended up receiving surprise bills many months after her visit, which makes me nervous that the same could happen to me. I wish their pricing and insurance communication were more transparent up front. I had X-rays done and everything I was told looked great...a week later I had severe pain in one of my teeth that supposedly looked good on the x-ray and now I need a root canal. I'll have it done some place else now.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
{"input_id":"1e79feea-8894-4ea9-92fc-3a82d354d7f3","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/place/3rd+%26+Columbia+Dental+Seattle/data=!4m7!3m6!1s0x54906ab13ce5a1db:0xfcb67014ad4b6e49!8m2!3d47.6046295!4d-122.3328247!16s%2Fg%2F1w2ytlm6!19sChIJ26HlPLFqkFQRSW5LrRRwtvw?authuser=0\u0026hl=en\u0026rclk=1","cid":"18209865377428237897","title":"3rd \u0026 Columbia Dental Seattle","categories":["Dentist","Cosmetic dentist","Dental clinic","Dental hygienist","Dental implants periodontist","Dental implants provider","Emergency dental service","Endodontist","Teeth whitening service"],"category":"Dentist","address":"810 3rd Ave #200, Seattle, WA 98104","open_hours":{"Friday":["Closed"],"Monday":["8 AM–4 PM"],"Saturday":["Closed"],"Sunday":["Closed"],"Thursday":["8 AM–4 PM"],"Tuesday":["8 AM–4 PM"],"Wednesday":["8 AM–4 PM"]},"popular_times":{},"web_site":"https://3rdandcolumbiadental.com/?utm_source=GMBListing\u0026utm_medium=Organic","phone":"(206) 219-2587","plus_code":"JM38+VV Seattle, Washington","review_count":261,"review_rating":4.9,"reviews_per_rating":{"1":4,"2":2,"3":1,"4":6,"5":248},"latitude":47.604629499999994,"longtitude":-122.33282469999999,"status":"","description":"","reviews_link":"","thumbnail":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAEVX_ncMJyQd86oBW9ipGV4seuZKf1g3KLVZAlAJbDQJb4BUt2S0E-smvdE3RxFo97Hlv2YHKmBbbsTqU3cRn9SmE47C7u0eYqSkq0dQHZX7gXn2ryVTID2Bre4iQExojBxGKY=w408-h544-k-no","timezone":"America/Los_Angeles","price_range":"","data_id":"0x54906ab13ce5a1db:0xfcb67014ad4b6e49","place_id":"ChIJ26HlPLFqkFQRSW5LrRRwtvw","images":[{"title":"All","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAEVX_ncMJyQd86oBW9ipGV4seuZKf1g3KLVZAlAJbDQJb4BUt2S0E-smvdE3RxFo97Hlv2YHKmBbbsTqU3cRn9SmE47C7u0eYqSkq0dQHZX7gXn2ryVTID2Bre4iQExojBxGKY=w224-h298-k-no"},{"title":"By owner","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAFiAXoyh7h8H3yf-veY3qvmlnG7AgtBw2SeS-Gz-82JwOnJZGGqilKgwFEBZs423Yd8MfxN_uAzxDNekEF2vNjUHZ74jlW1XKFZPEVSm8v-vgpPH1bmwp4AKnUxUQf29X7WYys7=w224-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=PAufZehgU3DzG2U0b2dAHw\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=49.349945\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://3rdandcolumbiadental.com/book-an-appointment/?utm_source=GMBListing\u0026utm_medium=Organic","source":"3rdandcolumbiadental.com"}],"menu":{"link":"/url?q=https://3rdandcolumbiadental.com/%3Futm_source%3DGMBListing%26utm_medium%3DOrganic\u0026opi=79508299\u0026sa=U\u0026ved=0ahUKEwjuw7O0yr-UAxUjDEQIHdxIBh0QqRkIHSgQ\u0026usg=AOvVaw0EmgAa9mbKWCXbKTduUmEU","source":"3rdandcolumbiadental.com"},"owner":{"id":"117247482903840529077","name":"3rd \u0026 Columbia Dental Seattle (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117247482903840529077"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Central Business District","street":"810 3rd Ave #200","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98104","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true},{"name":"Language assistance","enabled":false}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Yubin Song","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVrYPlmlkZSoFgSGiuvHvLFVUONf-QG94kW7_RBm8F0jt3ocIEbA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you are an adult patient who is considering to get a Invisalign for the teeth you've been thinking about for your entire life, I highly recommend 3rd and Columbia Dental. As an adult starting a ortho treatment for the first time, I was initially nervous about the process but Dr. Park was very attentive and took time to come up with the plan that will address my concerns so I decided to start the treatment. My two main concerns were crowded lower anterior teeth and narrow upper jaw. Before starting the treatment, Dr. Park clearly explained the treatment plan, timeline, expected results. Their dental assistances are also experienced and knowledgeable. My attachments barely came off during the whole process. Even as a first time ortho patient, I felt the treatment plan was well thought out, precisely moving my teeth without causing excessive pain. I'm currently done with my initial treatment and waiting for refinements sets but I'm already very happy with the results so far. My teeth are more straight and my facial asymmetry is improved. I'm breathing better because my upper jaw was expanded more. Do your research and get a consultation but I really think it's not too late to get your teeth fixed in your 30's.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2h15SYs9nqPt65HWfK5Xed4ejORfuSnlTzjQOxgwIEWtjv67zMRPP4pi7N0CiJ8z-JUHQEeDWoIXjBNhKBwhK8H2zSV3ETqsVzg3s4RgUt-zIVfG9N6Ngi7grFagNjSZTpqe8AqzZulSxE=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-12"},{"Name":"Jayanth Kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXfSXt5VLuD3Hpkpq5aU4qAZH7zq6WWA004ldAmauO27ian_Yf7yQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellently run operation. From the Front-desk onwards, I had friendly smiling faces welcome me, and usher me in through the various steps that were required. The hygenist, Grace is exceptionally professional and patient. I haven't been to the dentist in a couple of years, post covid, and she took her time to do a tremendous job in cleaning my teeth.\n\nThe doctor was friendly, paid close attention to all my information that i had shared prior to visit, and was very friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable, in helping me understand my options. I got so lucky picking this spot. They're super good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gabby S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhkBfpR0ZfISI3z4Jzds82v2ivTL-pYgkm83HbiTXv0F1X7rN1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really awesome practice. The hygienist are nice, gentle with the cleaning, and walk you through with what they are doing. Dr. Park is so kind and explains things in a digestible way. The office staff is friendly and helpful too. Would definitely recommend this practice.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Asia Larkin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVdWVkgPQtNGXPu2gfmCRosotxujnPjI3kXEVvTDPlBzMVCrZXNUw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The team here is great. They keep you informed along every step. They were super proactive in communication and very friendly in office. As a new patient getting set up can be overwhelming but they made the whole process smooth. I left feeling confident about the work they did and appreciate the care they provided.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steve \u0026 Gwen Cover","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjEY4wlniFF9Z4zCH6udnX4U1xR1bvlI5wT_uKPuw6PenvMV4H=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I visited this office with an emergency while on travel. From my first call to Christine, I was seen within an hour. The appointment was on-time, smooth, and a great experience.  The doctor and team were very understanding of my situation and had me in and out so I could make a critical flight connection.  Thank you for being so kind.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brittany Bennett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUINsl5ep8d032-fGRoqAx_FERHMF7p7tkdQXM8boaXOzNHiC4RIg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Park and the team were great. Kind, thorough, and accommodating. They fixed my chipped front tooth after my exam even though I wasn’t scheduled for it, and it turned out beautiful!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matthew Fischer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK9SegaGemdtgVpya87mC85HTJyqFDbBJP1qJIY3SgWgr2Rrw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been to 3rd and Columbia dental more times in the last two years than I would like to count... my teeth :(  (cavities, cracked teeth, crown(s), cleaning) but every step of the way it has been an enjoyable experience!\nFrom walking into the office and immediately being greeted by the front desk staff, to a prompt check in and intake, taking your annual x-rays,  the procession of walking you to your chair (each space is pretty sectioned off so its like your own room). I've come to know a lot of the staff I normally see on a first name basis (heyyyy!), chairs are comfy, you get cute terminator glasses (see attached photo), a bib, and you're off to whatever you need to do.\nDr. David Park is just beyond, a professional and very sweet man.  Efficient, honest, and it's all just so easy. I have fallen asleep and laughed here more times than I would like to count with my mouth WIDE open.\nAnyways, just go, your teeth will thank you. Use your insurance, the dentist (especially when you look into the eyes of this one) isn't scary, and we all swoon for a beautiful smile.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3cdhA9e-4za1YQYEv3NfG2PlkLWPXjCtguXzHPuSWjflrbiTeZSkz4vv0G-YaaF49afiDnOXz5Az3GvmLnjVrEA2XDyoSiOAvt3moLTnsYa2XCP-D6-jLZ4e5Avgc9nXXRXu9JqqU1FjLj=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-30"},{"Name":"Joonhyuk Yun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYeXjXjKFz8HNOE5w33ba3PZn073n007vEcknp7BZ_GhyVAw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The doctor and assistant were so kind and friendly! The doctor did a thorough dental exam but kept it quick and efficient.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
