AU3btJCQk7waSCPtPp_nKpDx9YoeBSep3V5gLCispbfmJkhQ8=w224-h298-k-no-pi0-ya351.09354-ro-0-fo100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"104792572585471673646","name":"Avenue Smiles (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104792572585471673646"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Denny Triangle","street":"2001 8th Ave #130","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98121","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Pediatric care","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Anushk Kh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJw5hS1wsSf-D2T5Y4Qv8kXXjtSRyK8BAJLjqxFtv-Cr7RSTw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr kim is one of the sweetest amd most accommodating\nDeby and front desk is kind too\nAlways had a very calm experience and they adjusted the material multiple times even though i was throwing up alot during the crown build up process\nWith dr kim the entire process is peaceful\nWould really recommend dr kim for a person who might fear dentists. He is an amazing dentist and person","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Camille Galit Cohen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXEHjWo5kvgNh-l6_9bE2mmAiErs5IuzJaSfOjHrheuVc_JSz91qg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I have been coming here for 3 years and have had good experiences with the doctor. Leaving 2 stars as I had a terrible experience with the dental assistant. She was rude and made me feel incredibly uncomfortable. One of them struggled a lot to take my x-rays, I kept telling her it was painful and she kept moving slow. Patients are in a vulnerable space and this dental assitant did not help with making the environment comfortable.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Angela D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVu9kh9dWpQoTiYW11PJjE0h5w65VE7r3qhGJxwEZ4mqDY_YQaQSw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The front desk is not doing their job. They told me I’m late. But it turned out to be someone else. When they do x-rays, they cut my mouth while putting the device in my month. It took me months to recover from the wounds. Bad service and they overcharge on my insurance, delta dental. Be aware","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ananya Tandon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK4q4pYVTCFgJVna80WazgEHLCwq0kbn5zxGnaLjdBOB971X0sW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The dentist and cleaning part was ok so I am leaving 2 stars. But experience with the front desk and hygienist/assistant was straight up bad.\n\nWhen the hygienist was taking xrays, it was just painful, she kept telling me thats normal, i told her very politely that Ive had dental X-rays many times in the past and it never hurt like this but she kept telling me I had a “small mouth” and what they do here is a full mouth X-ray, which other dental offices don’t do. I didn’t understand what she meant by full mouth in the beginning but looking at the X-rays later it just meant they look at all your teeth and roots, which all dentist offices have done for me, I even had those done multiple times a year when I was on Invisalign and it never hurt like this. We had to stop the X-ray at one point because it was too painful for me. She kept telling me multiple times that I need to “bite down hard” even though it was clearly hurting me. I was literally holding back tears.\n\nThe front desk called me on the day of my appointment to reschedule ( i had this appointment booked for a month and was receiving repeated texts and emails for reminders) but they wanted to change it last minute to 2 hours earlier. I told them I cant do that because I had planned they day around the appointment time already, so they told me they “might” have to reschedule and I can keep this appointment for now. When i reached 15 mins before my actual appointment, without even asking my name the front desk person told me they had called to reschedule, I didn’t pick up and Im 15 mins late. It turned out to be a mixup, they were thinking Im a different patient, but looking at other reviews here seems they tend to reschedule appointments last minute and the tone of the person when they called me earlier and when I reached for my appointment was rude.\n\nUpdate: removing one star because my mouth is still irritated and cut at different places a week after the xrays i took here. It’s still so painful. Literally the worst experience Ive ever had at a dentist.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sonam Khemlani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXkafi_oGWLro2s_jLCASGCMfDy3TDvM82OwyJ66seNg6OQzP9j8w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a great experience at Avenue Smiles - and like many, I don't like going to the dentist. Check-in is quick and efficient, and you don't wait more than a few minutes before being seen. Sarah at reception is very responsive and organized.\n\nEvan assisted with my fillings - he helped me feel relaxed and would constantly check in with me. Mel assisted with my cleaning - she is truly a gem! She was friendly, explained the process, and gave me a lot of insights into best dental hygiene practices. Dr. Kim was gentle, quick and very skilled - he was able to maneuver without me opening my mouth too much. Everyone was constantly checking in to ensure I was comfortable. Appointments are scheduled for an hour, but took less. It was as seamless and comfortable as it possibly could be. Would recommend to anyone who is looking for a new dentist!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daanish Ahmed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXS84NeWyPi-ux_4cYrwipAT7VC7DGMDMVkueam649bMDwKzdoO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"my fav dentist! everyone there is so sweet","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Parker Sing","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKqnbHjB1az13vaU0IdE1XqpXxkUg7REzy1zhMVfk5NphgUg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great experience with Dr. Kim and Evan! Service was fast and efficient! I’m actually looking forward to the next time I’m coming in which seems like a crazy thing to say about a dental appointment.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Céleste I","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUwCQGndT0gvESyqLGSKbDw6PIS3efYLK6fD6lH1YXEjKRMtE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Kim and his hygienists are all very nice and knowledgeable. My mouth is a bit sensitive. But I’ve always had a great experience here, and they are very gentle. Sarah, the receptionist, is also very nice and prompt in replying and emergency rescheduling. This place is also LGBTQIA+ friendly 🏳️‍🌈🏳️‍⚧️! Highly recommend! 😌","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
