26pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"116843395886348046732","name":"West Edge Dental, Jessica J. Emard DMD (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116843395886348046732"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Central Business District","street":"88 Spring St #100","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98104","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid parking lot","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Christine Hatcher","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDMpYfJNB5liksSV-3-lY7rDEn2e4vsqaIuWhr8HFGmQcLFxc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"West Edge has been taking care of my dental needs for many years now. Dr. Emard has a gentle touch and is so kind, and Danielle is a walking encyclopedia of all things oral hygiene-related! I love the team here and they love my teeth.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"v vibe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIGP6F8Rcyqg8AMVmiZWJ9ZlGiSn4RMd2V9E1hLwVK8CrbIlQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"It's great that she's a zero-covid dentist - those are very hard to find. But it is very uncool to use that advantage to twist the knife on financially disadvantaged patients. I told her I was unemployed and would need to take the treatments in smaller increments. She scheduled me for a cleaning estimated ~$400. I arrived prepared for the treatment, but she impulsively changed the plan and went straight for the expensive treatment. Midway through the procedure I realized she was going beyond just a cleaning and she didn't have a good answer for why she decided to switch the treatments around. Anyway, ~$1500 later, ok, she did a fine job filling some cavities and doing some cosmetic work. But I was only financially ready for a $400 bill and she changed the plan dramatically without consulting me. Won't be going back if I can help it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"R Kangas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHlSAUp815Cq7MnOXMKK-OmIeB9KRee-pu2f1D86CumH0mww=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been coming here and seeing Vanessa and Dr Emard for many years and they always give the best advice, and my teeth have never felt so taken care of at any dental office. I love the vibe of the office, and love many of the other hygienists when I need to get in for rescheduling.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Phil Clark","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV6_ZQe_Z0xPMK3DbhmLQBZ6ufDZsPacaJeHj1FRZ4ui-Kpd5hW=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Emard and Wendy have been my go-to dental team for years and consistently set the bar for exceptional care. After I moved away, I ran into a serious issue with older dental work, and Dr. Emard took the time to revisit my history and re-examine the situation. Rather than suggesting a quick fix, she recommended a comprehensive approach that prioritizes long-term stability.\n\nHer thoughtful, evidence-based guidance helped me avoid future complications and significant expense. What impressed me most was her unwavering integrity—always putting what’s clinically best for the patient first, even when it meant choosing the more conservative route.\n\nIf you’re looking for a Seattle dental practice that combines genuine warmth, clinical expertise, and true patient advocacy—long after you’ve left the office—you won’t find better than Dr. Emard and Wendy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"marco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFB65K9AgYf7BNF4E3k2zctOT4QnZG8Hrf_pxMxZ97bFB4VfnG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best dentist experience of my life! I have moved around a lot and been to dentists around Washington / other states. Nothing compares to West Edge Dental. The staff is skillful, knowledgeable, and kind too. They seem to really care about their craft and they are truly great people. I had been to this dentist many years ago before leaving the area and my experience returning has been consistent. They use modern techniques and tools, keeping you confident in their care. West Edge Dental is really in a league of its own.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brandon M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJEYoflhTPHumfTBMsDlBGrIJ1Tp3YhYE_xZp2RtycSb9Akww=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful staff, they always provide clear instructions. Everyone is always smiling under their masks and they welcome everyone as family. I usually dread going to the dentist but since I’ve started visiting West Edge Dental I look forward to them!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"James Ford","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJUFCWTPpdZQgExguVULIzz9mx0sJN9dtYkoig42t4ZYR-p9w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My dental hygienist is Danielle and she has taken great care of me. I have not been in good care and received top notch service until I found west edge dental. Hats off to Dr Emard and her great staff","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joshua Lozensky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.goog