ed":true},{"name":"Paid parking lot","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Gabrielle Llacuna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhvYYVMVEeoZyKnHEqg559hGRa3IpgBiTO628KNweZ1gymt0mk9A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Today was my first visit with Amato Dental, and I was so impressed with the entire experience. I’m typically a little nervous at dental appointments, but Michelle, my hygienist, was incredibly kind, patient, and reassuring. She explained each step as she went, which really helped me feel comfortable—and she did an excellent, thorough cleaning.\nDr. Tse was also wonderful—professional, personable, and very detailed in his exam. The front office staff and dental assistant were equally friendly and welcoming, which made the whole visit smooth and stress-free. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Greg Snyder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIL7ESQl2ZWDB0ssNfQ8yN1kj99JS9YsctLMx61Rg9qwJ5VVw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amato Dental Group has a great atmosphere and wonderful staff. Jessica and Maddy in the front office are super friendly and even though I arrived early they got me back to a chair right away to start my appointment which I didn’t expect and was impressed by.\nThe clinic is very organized, clean and has nice views of SODO. Yareli did a great job explaining everything she was going to do and what to expect as this was my first appointment with them and I appreciated that.\nDr Amato performed a detailed exam, took the time to get to know me and asked if I had any concerns about my teeth. He has a warm personality, was fun to talk to and I felt at ease the entire time.\nChelsea was my hygienist and her cleaning was quite simply the best I’ve ever received. It’s self evident she has a lot of experience for she communicated throughout the process, conducted a very precise thorough cleaning, and had a delicate touch with her instruments. She removed some plaque in a difficult location that my previous hygienist had missed and I was very thankful for that. It had been close to a year since my last cleaning and I was grateful that she took the necessary time needed to get my teeth clean.\nOverall my first visit was a very positive one, all of the staff I met were great, and I’m excited to be a patient at this practice.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelly Wolff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnz3cTXrrQtzZigovKJWV-pnxc9eCW2AfC-UUJJ3a1ALb2jMU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best dentist ever!  I love going to the dentist, and Dr. Amato is so fabulous that after moving out of state I still fly to Seattle twice a year for dental care!  I started seeing Dr. Amato around 2014 and he is always implementing the latest cutting edge technology and everyone is very friendly and hygienist Michelle is my favorite but I’ll see any of them as they are all highly skilled!  Never discomfort and every service is very thorough!  I can’t recommend this company more!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rie Timmerman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKg80nrQhHZPRIobYewtochcnwri5nzVg5mi0rkskSMwiaV5w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had one of the most thorough exams ever.  Every person in the office from the receptionist to the hygienists and dentists were extremely kind and courteous.  Michelle my hygienist was especially wonderful.  She is truly passionate and knowledgeable about dental health and has a delicate touch.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Farah Ahmed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWh8TzlFqLFePhxiqCFObPjK6nKdBkmzaMU36B107ZSwQJ-gbzS=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been a patient at Amato Dental Group for 4 years, and every visit has been exceptional. Each appointment is a fantastic experience  the staff is friendly, appointments start on time, and the care is consistently outstanding.\nDr Amato and the entire team are truly the best. I wouldn’t go anywhere else!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Catherine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvYkjDq8xkg_8jAGgEYC_YQfjZV6dmRQgqirsj21HLW6D5qbM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Always an exceptional experience! From the moment I am greeted by Maddy and Tiffany at the reception desk to my thorough cleaning with Chelsea to my exit with Mary and Jessica, I am well cared for and treated like family. This office is simply the best! And Dominique always stops by to say hi. Such a wonderful experience!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kellie Craine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3q6ZUocvYhUsUVVz5NNKyozM0N7IkwV91-P_qPyxc47LrkA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Amato and Chelsea have been taking excellent care of me for years. It is a privilege to see them every six months. I feel very fortunate to be in their care. I love these two. And the reception staff is outstanding.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Patty Romano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIkLfcS8qgW4qtP9cgdNmwRevCTj9-mVMJnCEL8e1tQ2ieh29_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Moving to a new city means finding new providers, and I feel like I hit the jackpot after my first visit to Amato Dental Group. Got a painless and skilled cleaning by Crystal, and a thorough evaluation and treatment by the rest of the team and Dr. Tse. Front office staff is friendly and efficient, and it’s always a bonus when an office runs on time. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
{"input_id":"1e79feea-8894-4ea9-92fc-3a82d354d7f3","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Smile+Art+by+Jaime+Lee+DDS/data=!4m7!3m6!1s0x54906ac95d751101:0x9cf345a53fda61c0!8m2!3d47.6087535!4d-122.3251012!16s%2Fg%2F1tffz645!19sChIJARF1XclqkFQRwGHaP6VF85w?authuser=0\u0026hl=en\u0026rclk=1","cid":"11309459665300644288","title":"Smile Art by Jaime Lee DDS","categories":["Dentist","Cosmetic dentist","Dental clinic","Dental implants provider","Emergency dental service","Teeth whitening service"],"category":"Dentist","address":"901 Boren Ave #1030, Seattle, WA 98104","open_hours":{"Friday":["Closed"],"Monday":["8 AM–4 PM"],"Saturday":["Closed"],"Sunday":["Closed"],"Thursday":["8 AM–4 PM"],"Tuesday":["8 AM–4 PM"],"Wednesday":["8 AM–4 PM"]},"popular_times":{},"web_site":"http://www.smileinseattle.com/","phone":"(206) 325-7200","plus_code":"JM5F+GX Seattle, Washington","review_count":259,"review_rating":4.7,"reviews_per_rating":{"1":14,"2":4,"3":2,"4":5,"5":234},"latitude":47.6087535,"longtitude":-122.32510119999999,"status":"","description":"","reviews_link":"","thumbnail":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAH5YIdUfEkKB0XrxbHZ62zwvraS-OfdCrP6xLJdhsr5iJGA8z13oymQYFRAjxjpOJ3Ub5D6vbfcjE6VLi_NTWHQEXjdx2tNSQjU-rMPT7GILN3IY1pQGwyel6yJlCj5CtqX6o7r=w408-h272-k-no","timezone":"America/Los_Angeles","price_range":"","data_id":"0x54906ac95d751101:0x9cf345a53fda61c0","place_id":"ChIJARF1XclqkFQRwGHaP6VF85w","images":[{"title":"All","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAH5YIdUfEkKB0XrxbHZ62zwvraS-OfdCrP6xLJdhsr5iJGA8z13oymQYFRAjxjpOJ3Ub5D6vbfcjE6VLi_NTWHQEXjdx2tNSQjU-rMPT7GILN3IY1pQGwyel6yJlCj5CtqX6o7r=w447-h298-k-no"},{"title":"By owner","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHLehlYnOkmDlqcbp73INX3yv8OtUDRsqpp_dUPzsq7u1TgisK7Fvnetc6n1DpzEEJcrEtL-Wk0lEv20XIRYaFnU2FJllXNG_CRnQmwV3ZqsK5yNN6gzbPywUIn15sKJlIDCRkV=w447-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=o_GwkoBnKZhdvj31KWutaw\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=247.64304\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://smileinseattle.com/contact/","source":"smileinseattle.com"}],"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"108527047500922805803","name":"Smile Art by Jaime Lee DDS (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108527047500922805803"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Downtown Seattle","street":"901 Boren Ave #1030","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98104","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Kent Kubani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUP6Vr2uiA6IIxMSXLbCPnBMAerALA7hC97wBFiVwR12t3NZMRE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Last year, I began a series of dental procedures recommended by and under the care of Jaime Lee DDS at Smile Art. Following her professional recommendation that I receive 14 fillings and 2 root canals (sounds insane, I know), we began treatment in early December 2024.\n\nAfter multiple appointments that were cancelled or postponed by the office, in January 2025 I began to suspect something was not right. While my teeth were in the middle of two root canals that had not been completed after 3 infections and multiple appointments to \"finish\" the treatment, I received second opinions of the care, which lead me to opt for an emergency tooth extraction and an emergency repeat root canal procedure to save another tooth (and the surrounding teeth, due to an uncontrolled infection). During my visits with my new providers (one general dentist, one endodontist) I was informed that based on my account of the care I had recieved during my visits at Smile Art, the standard of care was not followed. I was not I have never had any serious dental issues outside of a filling every couple of years.\n\nMy trust, my wallet, and my body were violated, and I had three dental insurance plans that were drained (one for the 2024 calendar year, and two for the 2025 calendar year). I received a partial refund for services that I never received (but was charged for anyways) but it took months of calling and emailing the office to hear back. I was still charged thousands of dollars for dental work that ultimately lead to losing a tooth and having to pay for an entirely new root canal. I strongly suggest that new patients reconsider placing their dental care in the hands of an individual like Jaime Lee.\n\nAlso, I have no way of confirming this outside of using context clues, but I believe many of the recent 5-star reviews for this business seem fake. They offer vague praises of the \"beautiful office\" and \"warm\" environment from the staff, but are by Google accounts that have odd names, no profile pictures, and have only left one review.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Hong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIBhBJwOI9ke-rxahq8gyzBTog62sZF75fWAZm8qsNfiUzLIBMq=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely love Dr. Jaimie and the team! Been trying to find a trusting dentist in the greater Seattle area. All the cleanings have been so gentle. I would highly recommend visiting as I already have referred friends and family to Dr. Lee!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nathan Duma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLx13IvXzbCDE77L858KumFR3IRlYs-bAx8DAJrGJ3IPSXc6UAZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had a disappointing experience at this dental office. During my visit, the dentist told me I needed multiple procedures—including several cavity fillings, redoing multiple existing fillings, and even suggested I get braces. They said, \"if you were family, I would tell you to get braces\" which felt more like pressure than genuine care.\n\nThe front desk staff were extremely smooth and salesy. It felt like they were more focused on convincing me to book treatments than on my actual dental health.\n\nThankfully, I decided to get a second opinion from my long-time dentist back in my home country—someone I’ve trusted for over 20 years. After a thorough check, they confirmed that everything was just fine except for one partial redo of a filling. No cavities, no need for multiple fillings, and definitely no need for braces.\n\nThis experience left me questioning whether the recommendations I received were based on necessity or profit. I would recommend getting a second opinion before agreeing to any major treatment here.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kevin Alldredge","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL2WxwABvuZdVnLG7d6dGRiYbsNvI8Ctb9TvSSk-qpyw2jofg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been with Dr. Lee for over 15 years - always puts me at ease. Does a fantastic job, I’m getting implants, so it’s a 3 part process over several months. The process has been steady \u0026 very professional.\n\nAlso a shout out to Jasmine as well. Very nice to see and immediately puts me at ease for these procedures…..makes sure I’m comfortable and ready to go.\n\nOverall fantastic","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paige Powers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgAwlz2xbTy1Jpq-vi-31GxhhGsrP1R83C3p4bQ-qzIrqHp-jT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been going to Smile Art by Jaime Lee for over a year now, and have had an absolutely wonderful experience! From the first moment I walked in, I felt welcomed and cared for by Dr. Lee and her team. Dr. Lee always takes the time to truly listen to my needs and concerns, which makes me feel completely at ease during my visits. Dr. Lee always takes the time to explain all of my treatment options in detail, ensuring that I fully understand each option, that I am an active participant in deciding my treatment plan, and that I am confident in my decision. Dr. Lee's level of care and attention to detail is exceptional, and I’m so glad I found this office. Highly recommend to anyone looking for a dentist who truly cares about their patients!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexis Aldrich","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXEZ7hbzBhVPeKXlqhRekHdyb30DHqbrr1i8OgFvM7MO1o9Sm8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a former dental assistant I’m so incredibly picky when it comes to choosing the best of the best dentist for my dental needs. Dr Jaime is a rare find and I travel across state anytime I need treatment or routine care. She has decades of experience yet she’s not jaded and constantly adorns her office walls with new credentials and qualifications. She implements the most current state of the art technology such as digital impressions, in office crowns, and digital x-rays to give\nher patients the best care available. Her office is gorgeous with an amazing view, very clean and luxuriously comfortable. Did I mention she’s also a painter and artist and you may see a few pieces of her original artwork in the office. Her staff is so amazing, caring, and talented. The team is so fast and every treatment is efficient and comfortable. The work she has previously done has lasted decades and I really trust she cares about her work and health of her patients. She really takes the time to listen to me, educates, and offers options and a dental plan to reach my goals. Once you get to know her she’s just an amazing person. She does a lot of charity work and volunteers and has a big heart. I wouldn’t trust anyone else with my care! You guys rock! ❤️","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Seth Aldrich","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIFYU4QZu1vqEY_KSsyQdDIURqDAqVgP0MFEPAkvO2KAZA2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Without a doubt, this is the finest dental office I've ever had the pleasure of visiting. I’ve been a patient at Dr. Jamie’s practice since I was a child, and each visit has consistently been a positive and uplifting experience. The welcoming atmosphere, coupled with the exceptional care provided by the staff, has made every appointment feel comfortable and reassuring","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sophie Mora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKFV7PiEB2A5fn7BIc6qMo2zqESbOPuum02oAlsg7twjgEMfA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My experience at this practice has been downright frustrating and bewildering. Dr. Lee started two root canals on my teeth and months and several appointments later still wouldn’t place the crowns let alone finish the actual root canals. It took going to two other dentists (and a trip to the ER due to so much pain) to learn that these should have been done by an endodontist in the first place. The first temporary filling that was placed started to break down in my mouth after they cancelled my appointment 15 minutes before and couldn’t reschedule me for weeks. They also did not use proper hygiene by neglecting to isolate the tooth being worked on by a dental dam. Throughout all of these appointments I was confused and frustrated with the poor communication by Dr. Lee.\n\nMy insurance was billed for root canals that were not done and I paid out of pocket for things that were also not completed. Now, nobody at the office will reply to my emails regarding the thousands I paid for services not completed. It feels like as a patient here you have to ask over and over what is going on, when will things be completed and advocate for yourself just to get information on what’s going on with your teeth. No thanks. Writing this so others can avoid this headache.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
