name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"crowd","name":"Crowd","options":[{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Checks","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Paid parking lot","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Riddhi Bhide","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrpEwAmgFcEVxxjmAr3t81aOwS6kY1otAPTJLKuuZEj5nYbGxRqg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently took my one-year-old for their very first dental appointment at Mortis Shin Dentistry  of Seattle and I couldn't be more impressed. From the moment we walked in, the front desk staff and the hygienist were absolutely delightful and made my child feel so comfortable. I had been bracing myself for tears and screaming—especially since my little one has recently become very protective of their mouth—but the experience was the complete opposite.\nDr. Shin and the entire team were incredibly patient. Even though it took a while for my child to feel ready to open up, they never rushed us; they simply waited and stayed encouraging. It is so reassuring to find a practice that is truly family-oriented and handles all age groups with such care. Plus, the central location is a huge bonus—it's wonderful not having to drive miles for such high-quality care for a child as young as one. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rainbows2Rain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUoDTA46asvt7DkyDOswxFbCx_WGvjfKOWtPPdICuK65HYxQtM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Shin and his team are excellent. They are skilled at what they do, and seem to really prioritize patient comfort. During my last cleaning I was  so relaxed that my oura ring thought I took a 30 minute nap. They do not try to  “upsell” with unnecessary procedures like many other dentists unfortunately do, and their Invisalign pricing is very fair.  Dr. Shin is young, highly trained and takes the time to ask questions/listen to patients.i completely trust his judgement and his technical skills, and the hygienists are the best I’ve ever experienced. Parking is easy on the surface lot by the building or at Pacific Place. There is valet parking for the building if needed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jimin Yoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUL4N8crCmyljqXcKOTEpF3DHPBcp41eN4tHKFS94qAZrhMS0FJrw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had such a great experience with Dr. Shin! He helped me with my broken molar and root canal, and the whole process was completely painless. He was very gentle, kind, and made sure I felt comfortable the entire time. I really appreciated his professionalism and care — I highly recommend Dr. Shin 👍👍👍","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"T S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVGiEkyCw1bUql-vcbSb3MYQoPpc2ajVQve4nyszxf-pBRa439N=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have a hard time feeling comfortable at the dentist so I’ve been looking for a dentist who is convenient to me and that I feel comfortable with. From the first visit, I’ve been so pleased. The staff is extremely kind and patient and Dr Shin is wonderful. He takes time to talk you through things, gives you options and recommendations but most importantly, he starts by asking me about what I want. This has been the biggest difference. With a lot of my other dentists I often feel that if I don’t comply with their recommendation, it makes it awkward to continue seeing them. Not with Dr Shin. He is also very thorough, gentle and very caring. The hygienists are the same and I can tell from their rapport, that Dr Shin treats them as peers and not just subordinates.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Antwan Williams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLXNp98hU6iDXA1hESn7QO0W40vWJ2JcBayawidnyKwFa04dc4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"One thing I care about-- is my experience. I can confidently say that, Breanna, I believe shes the office manager did her due diligence to ensure I had a horrible experience.\n\nI came in for an issue with anticipation of getting all of my work done here at the office. I had some changes with work, which means that I couldn't be there due to business needs and lets be honest, in this economy we are prioritizing work. Also, I wasn't in any agony or pain at the moment. I reached out on the 22nd saying that I would not be able to make it due to work. My appointment was on the 24th. This is a office that is only open Monday-Thurday so it's super hard to give that notice during business hours. She didn't try to understand anything that I was saying, she didn't try to hear me out, just flat out said no. Emergencies happen all the time. No one will be able to make all appointments and other things will take priority. I truly hate the way I was treated and 100% will not be spending my resources here.\n\nI hope the $150 fee was worth the thousands that I was planning to pay to fix my smile. Again, I care about my experience, how I am being treated, and how someone helps me navigate in a space that I am not a SME in.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ariel van Spronsen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXig7SWUu7gto24j-Nbw4tG54uylrz5qJb7n4o2xicejusUz9IGfw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was a patient of Dr. Alan Moritis for over 20 years, and continued with his daughter Dr. Julia Moritis when she took over the practice. Now under the care of Dr. Harry Shin, I continue to be a happy patient. I appreciate their measured approach to dental care - they don’t push procedures unnecessarily but are also proactive when they’re needed. The docs explain things well and always involve me in decision-making. The office is clean and up to date, and the views from their 15th floor downtown office aren’t too shabby either! I also appreciate that they invest in technologies that are purposeful rather than trendy, so If you’re looking for maximum technology bling I’d say look at other practices.\n\nBecause of the great preventive care I’ve received here over the last 25+ years I haven’t had many restorative  procedures, but the one root canal and two fillings I’ve done here were painless and complication-free.\n\nI highly recommend Moritis Shin Dentistry. solid, thoughtful, trustworthy lifelong dental care!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hyunju Oh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLqVlwusyglQ1hk2QwVZo4HDYAl9k69On_TDzUoIzaX8tYOuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Shin is truly an exceptional dentist — kind, gentle, and incredibly thorough. He takes the time to explain every step of the process and makes you feel completely at ease, even during more involved procedures. His attention to detail and calm demeanor create an environment of trust and comfort, and it’s clear he genuinely cares about his patients’ well-being. I always leave feeling confident that I’ve received the highest level of care. I’m so glad to have found Dr. Shin and wouldn’t hesitate to recommend him to anyone looking for a compassionate and skilled dentist.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Becca Robinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUX0KYadtU-6GSitEh5c4EILSVfAVBk4h7d-_mA5ixCWLktBYs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent practice with attentive, caring staff whose tenure has spanned multiple decades with our family. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
