:"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=uWhTWhQvHWVjhCpSrmiEeQ\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=246.11317\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://flexbook.me/smilespace?rwg_token=AFd1xnGQ4OMb6O6l5uft3oskA34uU3iGBbt6wL02dgcmhAs-RxOnd8_zOwy488R0EgWtv-yKwNRJ21auFzEEQrTmY4cdpnr_bud7KHX4G1ej2XsLf_CnbDE%3D","source":"flexbook.me"}],"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"102582519762257899347","name":"The Smile Space (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102582519762257899347"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Belltown","street":"2911 2nd Ave Ste 106","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98121","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Nuby He","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqsdklS5j9aJsrNiHkb50xndQzXt7oKPQ_Nu6DMkbqwt2AIEQK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"[Update] They investigated the scheduling issue thoroughly and followed up professionally. I appreciate the transparency and explanation:)\n\n[Jan 2026] This is the fifth time I’ve come here for an appointment, and when I checked in, they told me I wasn’t on the schedule. The frustrating part is that I received reminder emails and text messages confirming the appointment, and the date/time were correct. Yet the front desk still said I wasn’t booked.\n\nThey couldn’t do anything except reschedule, and the staff expressed her apology and said “that happens.” Honestly, this should not be happening. It’s extremely disrespectful of patients’ time, especially when we plan our day around an appointment.\n\nLast time I came here, I arrived on time but still waited about 30 minutes. I understand delays can happen since treatment time isn’t always predictable.\n\nBut a scheduling error like this should never happen.\n\n[Dec 2025] This was my third time coming here. Thuy is very friendly and patient in answering my questions—wonderful staff overall! Iris is very professional in assisting Dr. Alina and was thoughtful in taking care of my lips with Vaseline. Dr. Alina did an great job filling my cavity and showed great kindness when I had questions about my fillings and tooth irritation. I would definitely come again!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0y9nkntwP5Zg0cyfXBTwRS8WSK9AwT-KS5giwGOw61AqYjHiq_rtPouTO468AdoAGzbOOp1QlzoEDtgUfrLkWC1VSJLn3MffTeVUj1l9jxuniGGULFZqtrsOoK9O8GIt7WNkU9IXpEGNQT=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-13"},{"Name":"Bruce C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJEOsgWrNpb5JSEwnPy3DgAOIU3lELN_j1hdgEEwB4L0-0iJQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been working with Dr. Christina for a few months, and I’ve always appreciated how thoughtful and patient she is. During the time we work together, she consistently took the time to explain things carefully and helped me understand what was happening step by step.\nEven during moments when I felt anxious or unsure, she remained calm, kind, and professional. I always felt that she genuinely cared about my well-being and wanted the best for me.\nI’m grateful for the time and energy she invested in my case. She is a compassionate doctor who truly puts her patients first. I highly recommend Dr Christina to any other patients.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rose Ridder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJI2J3Eyjup-vQcaN-IdaeuAseeHmLGg9keqhsPvcgBhUV5ug=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just got my teeth cleaned - the cleaning was great - very thorough x-rays and exam, cleaning with water at the perfect temperature, and very friendly. One thing to be cautious of is prior approval from your insurance. I was not contacted before the appointment to be alerted that my insurance hadn't been confirmed, and they were still confirming the coverage when I started my appointment. The cash price for an initial visit is $413, so that bill upon exit was startling to say the least. However, they have been receptive to working with me because of that blindsiding, including use of their independent coverage system that has a monthly subscription model. So the moral of the story is: great dental care, but make sure the bill is confirmed *before* you start your visit, even if you have provided your insurance information!\n\n(Review updated because the clinic was willing to work with me to fix the billing issue).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Natasha Gray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGh6sa8wfLfGgNuXU3AevZAHVEn-aWvxEuvKPige0j8YGHjUh6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely love The Smile Space! Dr. Maria Vallejos-Castillo is a true gem. She is incredibly caring and genuinely listens to my concerns and needs. Visiting the dentist usually makes me anxious, but everyone at The Smile Space, from the front desk staff to the assistants and dental practitioners, has been welcoming and supportive. They do everything they can to ease my nerves. I also appreciate the advanced technology they use and how they review my dental progress with me. Overall, my experience with The Smile Space has been very positive!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"H Reddy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLzEMj-1ob3r74a1hhF1x5C-wKJh3rBcpKdMNNf6zPBwDPn5A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I used to dread the dentist, but Smile Space changed that. Everyone there is so welcoming and kind.\n\nThuy at the front desk went above and beyond in helping me navigate insurance and patiently answered all of my questions.\n\nDr. Daniel Lee made all the difference. He genuinely cares about his patients and takes the time to explain procedures and treatment options thoroughly. During treatments, he’d pause to check in and was really understanding about my dental anxiety.\n\nIf you’ve had negative dental experiences in the past, I highly recommend giving them a try.\n\nBonus: they have a cute pup to keep you company while you wait.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alex Chiu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLLVtLt0RfDUUUeuO2v-MhCZO-e_CDxZLBQl7xIqyfaQD1spQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been to the Smile Space throughout my two years but my latest visit to Patrick there was excellent. He was thorough, communicative and professional. For my filling, he made sure that there was no pain, that every step along the way was documented and at the end demonstrated excellent craftsmanship on the filling. Going to the dentist never felt more reassuring. Thank you very much Patrick! Hope you see you again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Zizi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocINRvXNaa_Ajfj6bIlpoiES2xL2cGkeYMD_fPPKC1xDjZfeFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I first came in with my family for general dental and ortho, and now we introduce friends to this practice as well. Dr Christina is so professional, patient, and she well explains everything. She does everything she can to help achieve the best result, sometimes I asked too many questions, and she is still patient, warm in answering all of them. The office assistant Thuy is the best of the best, we never ever got any wrong billings, and every of our question was turned around swiftly like a breeze.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steven Pai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJf91uodYdsaxF-psTW4TCmgw3NxNIJ59tBKidgjdq_BI8dEw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you are like me and have terrible anxiety with going to the dentists (awful experiences when i was younger), fear not, everybody here makes an effort to make you feel comfortable! Everybody from the front desk to the techs to the doctor were extremely kind which i really appreciate. I saw Dr. Michou today, she was very friendly and really helpful with all of my questions.\n\nAlso, this is probably the best dental office i’ve ever seen in my life. It’s so clean and the technology they use is so new. They also have TVs on their ceilings so you can watch Netflix while they work on your teeth, definitely help with my anxiety a lot! They even got Aesop hand soap in the bathrooms, it’s really so nice here lol\n\nThanks again to everybody that helped me today!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
