:"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid parking lot","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Shervonne Barnett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJCems5C9Z8vJGLV_5cTVWBJeNZAY6tiH_1cMAIJV1EKA5j5w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Guys, I am totally petrified of Dentists. But the condition of my teeth wouldn’t let me put it off any longer. So I googled and found a place called Gentle Dental. And my goodness, they live up to their name! Everyone I interacted with was so kind. And my Dentist explained I would feel sensitivity due to the procedure. He was truly gentle, easy and slow. And Gentle Dental took my insurance. I hope my future appointments with them is as enjoyable.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sheryl Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW8IOt5g492C95QtotRnjbJ3H33GWlvmDhIzbEa4g_Tis5PTGEC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’d like to compliment the outstanding workmanship at Gentle Dental Capitol Hill. The dentist I saw last week was incredible, and the entire team and staff were equally impressive—professional, warm, and attentive. My tooth looks beautiful, and I couldn’t be happier with the results. I will absolutely continue using their services and highly recommend them.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mike Saechao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocITfPJ8AuxyT23sKcsI1xNao1JcZVPgXJSTvxZ0_XHUIDNMbOxm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My first initial appointment was about a month ago. The front desk/receptionist was great and very helpful.\n\nI had emailed my x-rays from my former dentist weeks before my appointment. I understand that they had to do their own x-rays, which they did. Moments later, someone came in, maybe it was a hygienist or assistant, who told me they spotted a new cavity. It was not a recent cavity, it was a filling. Big difference.\n\nThis confused me... Did they not look at my previous x-rays that I emailed them? I was told then, I needed my upper wisdom teeth pulled out, a deep cleaning and implants.\n\nMy upper wisdom teeth do not bother me. The deep cleaning yes. Implants, I am fine without them.\n\nIt didn't seem like they gave me a choice... and expected me to return within a week or two.\n\nThis gave me a lot of anxiety. I felt forced to schedule a follow up appointment. I did, though, I cancelled it due to feeling nervous about this whole experience.\n\nI wouldn't mind coming back, but perhaps, maybe a different dentist or who ever that person that read my x-rays.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Erin Bell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL-h8XF90gMNZhq_uMK8VVK4szTKKJLvdvMy0_te9MRoW04Nw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All-around great experience. I was a former patient of a different Gentle Dental location (now closed) and didn’t have the best experience. The Capitol Hill location was really great. The staff was highly communicative and friendly and they seem to have it running like a well-oiled machine. The dentist (Dr. Fletcher) was wonderful. Friendly, personable,  and he took time to explain thoughts, concerns, plan of action. He was straightforward and covered the whole best case:worst case scenarios. I never felt like they were pushing any procedures or extra services on me or my daughter-I’ve experienced this in the past with other dental providers.\n\nOverall-highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Erin Panichkul","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVB9isIO25ERCwh8ISF4EHLIArvOnq0uMGM15jSfo1yHzkL9bSf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Gentle Dental is my absolute favorite. I’m a bit of a sensitive Sally and the dentist made my experience pleasant and as painless as possible. I got a deep cleaning, filling, and laser/irrigation cleanse. Totally worth it! I love supporting this dental office as the dentist is a woman of color and she has a mostly POC staff. The receptionist and dental hygienist were also amazing. I felt extremely welcomed and valued with my individualized support. 11/10 would recommend to all my friends and fam.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bobby Bethke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4SOZNuxkkHcQt4j0uXxrRQPlQ4a03-9-8BRD_os-MiVpgpJgg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I've had quality care at Gentle Dental - when I can schedule it. Booking appointments is extremely difficult (they never pick up the phone unless you say you're a new patient, good luck getting through if you say you're an existing customer), and rescheduling is even harder. When I would finally go in for treatment, I always had a good experience.\n\nNone of these issues, however, matter to me because in December 2023 I was overbilled for my wisdom teeth removal surgery by $587. I was never notified of this insurance overcharge by Gentle Dental, and only discovered the mistake when I went in for a checkup and was asked if I wanted to pay with a patient credit I was completely unaware of. As far as I can tell, they never planned on refunding me, or even notifying me.\n\nSince then, I have been unsuccessfully trying to get my patient credit refunded. I've called their office many times, visited in person three times, and received no information beyond \"this is an insurance issue, we'll contact them but have no way to know if/when they'll refund you.\"\n\nIt's not an insurance issue: my insurer has been paid in full, and Gentle Dental has yet to give me back my $587 because apparently their mistake is my responsibility to fund, and my responsibility to fix.\n\nGood care, horrible scheduling, insurance billing malpractice.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Maddy Borowski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfFng7fQblKKIiyaXcVGRnlHJdvJlI41j2zVfhnnau3Tva8Cg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I received preventative care from Gental Dental Capitol Hill in January 2025, which was fully covered by my dental insurance. Worst experience I have ever had with a healthcare provider. For over 12 months, I have continued receiving bills claiming I owe $615 and threatening collections. I have called the number on the bill countless times, and each time I am told the issue is being handled and the claim will be submitted to insurance, but the bills never stop. I cannot find proper contact information for anyone in billing who can actually resolve this issue.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emily Bofto","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1J3KRIuYmiJqoVjcdJz-jI2hAqKV4BbUPjZw1a8oHYUDy8D4O=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just had my first appointment at Gentle Dental- and I am so impressed! I haven’t been to the dentist in many many years and finally wanted to tackle it and take care of my teeth. From Dr.fletcher to the hygienist (I didn’t catch her name, sorry) they were both so kind and took time to break everything down for me. There was no judgement at all. Truly can’t recommend them enough for scaredy cats like myself!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
