e 312","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98101","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Robert Hernandez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_B_J3Xopguf4J6o4WEMQQBq3FhK231nz4xr8LmNCa-SdLh54=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I just had my first visit with Dr. Andreea Larhs and I can honestly say it was one of the best dental experiences I've ever had. From the moment I walked in, the team made me feel welcomed, comfortable, and genuinely cared for.\n\nI came in for a tooth extraction, and the entire process was handled with such professionalism, expertise, and compassion that it completely exceeded my expectations. Dr. Larhs took the time to explain everything clearly, checked in on my comfort throughout the visit, and made what could've been a stressful procedure surprisingly smooth.\n\nWhat truly set this experience apart, though, were the thoughtful touches after the appointment. That evening, I received a personal text message from Dr. Larhs checking in on how I was feeling. Not an automated message, but an actual text from her personally . That level of care is incredibly rare and shows her dedication to providing world-class, patient-first service.\n\nThen, just two days later, I opened my mailbox to find a handwritten welcome letter from Dr. Larhs. Such a small gesture, but it spoke volumes about the culture, attention to detail, and genuine warmth of this office.\n\nIf you're looking for a dentist who goes above and beyond in every possible way, Dr. Andreea Larhs and her team are truly outstanding. I'm so grateful to have found this practice and can't recommend them highly enough!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kit Ciocio (Chity)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLy7Lz1vWWIOO8lWb-cxK0Mog5xM52pUSwUAkGOxr4PK84uRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"If you think you are going to a dentist with great credentials and education who will work on your teeth you might be in for a surprise.  Everyone in the office, but Dr. Lahrs will work on your teeth, many times without an introduction on who will do what.  I went for a filling replacement and after Dr. Larhs has checked my tooth, the assistant prepared the dam and everything else for the replacement of the old filling and without any introduction or notice, someone else appeared from the back of the chair and started working on my tooth. I did not even see the face of this person, but after checking their website to see if there is another dentist in this office, I found out that was someone with just a course/class in changing fillings. Not a dentist.  Needless to say, when Dr Lahrs came to check my new filling, something was wrong and she had to redo it. Very, very disappointing.  I felt cheated and speechless.\nI also went to change one of my old crowns and clean my teeth.  These appointments were as disastrous/dissapointing as the filling replacement.  Dr Lahrs does not seem to work on my teeth unless there is a problem created by her assistants.  Like, her assistant could not remove the crown from my tooth - she tried every tool she had including pliers, etc. for well over 45 minutes.  It was close to torture and my lips/mouth we're hurting. At last Dr Lahrs showed up and took out the crown very fast.\nAll appointments were at least one hour over the planned time.  Each time I was in there I was for at least 2 hours or longer.  A lot of chatting and protocols.  I am no longer going to her office as I would like the dentist I choose to work on my teeth (not the whole office).\nIf I could I could give it a zero stars review.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"M Gentry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJHDckyxCal4s0K41Z-8WaUKl8BSruS6BL4ffdRYR0mI59o=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome dentist. She uses state-of-the-art techniques, is very personable, and takes time to really explain what’s going on. I’ve referred several people to her and they’ve all been very happy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michelle AWS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3YCtp0ClGv9rTpbIodo4IsD-wwkC1XgOTEUW4a0Gm6dInFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the best dentist I have ever had in my entire life. I used to have the worst anxiety when visitng the dentist. I have been going here for almost ten years and I no longer have anxiety with the dentist.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Madison Carlyle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKe3HxFpgxGsX_1doMrxiyft3V8xiKFQ3gnjEeBN6rFmpMmQEv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
